    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I appreciate what you are saying, but if you think about the order of the segments & legend as 'first to last' rather than 'top to bottom', the current behavior makes sense. The first value is always the one nearest to the x-axis.\n\nImagine if the values of a, b, and c were all negative. 'Top to bottom' takes on a different meaning on the other side of the x-axis...or if the dataset was rendered as a horizontal bar chart.\n\n![image](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/134359/1968453/07a85898-82e3-11e3-946b-062999a1b0ab.png)\n"
  },
